title: 3 day First Great Western strike goes ahead after talks stall
text:
Credit: ITV West Country Rail journeys are returning to normal after three days of strike action on First Great Western services.
Members of the RMT union walked out over issues relating to the introduction of new high-speed trains.
After three days of reduced services and cancellations, many passengers were feeling frustrated.
